<h2>Kinsta vs SiteGround</h2>

The most common comparison. Short version: SiteGround is excellent value at $10-20/mo for sites that don't need top-tier performance. Kinsta is the right call when performance directly affects revenue -- e-commerce, content sites chasing Google rankings, or any site where downtime costs money.

For operator sites where Google search traffic is the growth engine, the Kinsta performance premium pays for itself in better rankings.

<h2>🏆 Final Verdict</h2>

Kinsta earns its premium price for operators running sites that matter. The performance is genuinely best-in-class, the support is excellent, and the dashboard makes managing multiple sites straightforward. If your WordPress site generates revenue or drives leads, the $35/mo starting price is justified.

